
15,01   Immanuel Kant was a real pissant
15,01        who was very rarely stable.
15,01   Heidegger, Heidegger was a boozy beggar
15,01        who could think you under the table.
15,01   David Hume could out consume
15,01        Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel,
15,01   And Wittgenstein was a beery swine
15,01        who was just as sloshed as Schlegel.

15,01   There's nothing Nietzsche couldn't teach ya
15,01       'bout the raisin' of the wrist.
15,01   Socrates himself was permanently pissed.

15,01   John Stewart Mill, of his own free will,
15,01        after half a pint of shandy was particularly ill.
15,01   Plato, they say, could stick it away,
15,01        'alf a crate of whiskey every day!
15,01   Aristotle, Aristotle was a bugger for the bottle,
15,01        and Hobbes was fond of his Dram.
15,01   And Rene Descartes was a drunken fart:
15,01        "I drink, therefore I am."

15,01   Yes, Socrates himself is particularly missed;
15,01   A lovely little thinker, but a bugger when he's pissed.
